description:
Dynamite Entertainment proudly presents the dynamic debut of Robocop by writer Rob (Classwar) Williams and artist Fabiano (MARVEL ZOMBIES VS. THE ARMY OF DARKNESS) Neves! Under two awesome covers - one by the sensational Stephen Segovia and the other by Dynamite's newest artistic sensation (and the pupil of artist David Finch) Johnny D! - Dynamite goes back to basics as it unveils the dystopian, deeply satirical, and all-out violent world of Robocop.

This is ROBOCOP meets the conspiracy theory mystery of ALL THE PRESIDENT'S MEN, following on from Paul Verhoeven's original by mixing high action, extreme violence and satire. Plus: the return of ED-209!
name: Revolution, Part 1

description: A new detective has hit the New York City streets... John McClane! He's got a new rank, a new partner and a new pain in the ass to deal with! A major crime is about to reveal itself. It all starts in a massage parlor then things just get seedier from there. Join legendary industry creator Howard Chaykin on a thrill ride that's rung up over $1 billion in box office worldwide and become the gold standard for classic action! Yippee Ki Yay!
name: Year One Part Five

description: Who is the Iron Axis and what makes them--yes, them--the deadliest foes Iron Man has ever faced? And what happens when the all-new, all-deadly Whiplash gets caught in the middle? Before he strikes in Iron Man 2, meet the latest version of this classic Armored Avenger foe in this in-continuity adventure!

Their interests include interspecies romance, modern art, and bloody murder. Everything is permitted, and so are they. Until they meet the original Young Avengers. And then their grey areas will come home to roost. Collects Dark Reign: Young Avengers #1-5.

description: Goku is shocked when he learns his true origins from Raditz. Raditz mocks Goku, calling him weak. He then kidnaps Gohan in order to provoke Goku into attacking him without mercy.

THE INVASION AIN’T DONE UNTIL THE FAT SKRULL SINGS! Pulled from the ashes of 1994 straight to the 21st century, the Skrull Kill Krew is back and more brutal than ever! Television writer and novelist Adam Felber (HBO’s REAL TIME; Schrodinger’s Cat) and superstar artist Paulo Siqueira (Ms.Marvel; Amazing Spider-Man) bring you a disturbing and violent tale of a man with a couple of big guns and a bunch of alien shape shifters who harken back to the earliest days of the Marvel Universe. Pull up a chain gun and join us, won’t you? Collecting SKRULL KILL CREW #1-5 and material from DARK REIGN NEW NATION.
 
Skrull Kill Krew #1 - Mutation Nation
Pulled from the ashes of 1994, straight to the 21st century, the Skrull Kill Krew is back more brutal than ever! Television writer and novelist Adam Felber (HBO's REAL TIME; Schrodinger's Cat) and superstar artist Paulo Siqueira (Ms.Marvel; Amazing Spider-Man) bring you a disturbing and violent tale of a man with a couple of big guns and a bunch of alien shape shifters who harkens back to the earliest days of the Marvel Universe. Pull up a chain gun and join us, won't you?

Skrull Kill Krew #2 - Apocalypse Cow!
The creepy spin-off of Secret Invasion continues with the Krew leader Ryder’s attempts to take down a faction of surviving scions of the original Skrulls that Reed Richards turned into cows. Unfortunately he’s got to deal with the fact that his team is dead first.

Skrull Kill Krew #3 - Harms Race
One Wolverine ain’t enough for ya? How about TWO? Depending how our story conference goes tomorrow…you might even get three! Evil Skrull scions! Massively malevolent cow meat! And a guy with a gun arm! This over-the-top follow-up to last year’s Secret Invasion continues with the return of more members of the Krew…including a white-supremacist who hasn’t read the paper in about a year. All brought to you by a writer for National Public Radio. Man, one of these things just ain’t like the other.

Skrull Kill Krew #4 - Cow Can't Help It!
It’s just a bloody mess as the ridiculously over-the-top Krew of Skrull Killers finally confronts an enemy that may be too much for them to handle. The cover has a cow with a gun mouth…and that’s nowhere NEAR the weirdest thing in the issue.

Skrull Kill Krew #5 - Slaughterhouse Five
It’s a Marvel Massacre as the Krew stands up the vestiges of a Skrull threat that won’t seem to die. Villains, aliens, and guy with a gun arm! Somebody up here likes you.

Dark Reign: New Nation #1 - New Nation
The Invasion is over, and the shape of the world has changed, with new and returning players now center stage. Get the lowdown on the SECRET WARRIORS, the AGENTS OF ATLAS, WAR WARCHINE, RONIN & MOCKINGBIRD, and the SKRULL KILL KREW, and learn how they fit into this brave new world in all-new stories setting up their upcoming titles.
name: Dark Reign: Skrull Kill Krew TPB

description: More comics for your cash! This issue's stories are even more super-sized! Cover-featured this time is Shadow Star with a 46-page episode! Shiina is returning from the island where she discovered Hoshimaru, her Shadow Star, when her plane is attacked by a Shadow Dragon! Can Shiina and little Hoshi protect the plane and its passengers? Also featured are 30 pages of 3x3 Eyes, plus What's Michael? and TWO Oh My Goddess! stories! All for under the price of two comic books! [Note: Seraphic Feather will return next issue; for now, enjoy the beatutiful pinup illo by Hiroyuki Utatane.]

Fan-favorite 3x3 Eyes is cover-featured this time, with an incredible battle between our heroes and an evil demon! In the next "lost episode" of Oh My Goddess!, Keiichi's friend Otaki is in love... unfortunately, he's an idiot! Can Belldandy's goddess power help him? Plus, more sci-fi suspense in Seraphic Feather, starfish from space in Shadow Star, and feline fun in What's Michael? The best deal in manga -- only from Dark Horse!

America's most popular manga anthology continues! On the front is the best-selling Oh My Goddess! with another rare, never-before-seen story. Also featured are 3x3 Eyes, which continues with the next chapter of "Flight of the Demon," and Shadow Star, featuring a super-sized 37-page episode! Plus, the next chapter of the stunning Seraphic Feather, and a short What's Michael? story rounds out another giant-sized issue. Don't miss the best entertainment value in manga -- only from Dark Horse!

What's Michael? is cover-featured this month, with not one, but three short stories! Watch as Michael helps a thief, frightens a Mafia criminal, and annoys the heck out of some television viewers! And in 3x3 Eyes, Pai and Yakumo battle a mammoth demon and try to recover the legendary "Figure of Man" statue. In Shadow Star, secrets are uncovered and mysteries unfold as Shiina and a friend learn about each other's alien starfish! Plus, evil is revealed on the moon in Seraphic Feather, and Megumi encounters the Earth Spirit (Third Class) in another "lost" episode of Oh My Goddess! It's five full-length features for one low price, only from Dark Horse!

America's favorite manga anthology returns, with another giant issue of cover-to-cover comics! Shadow Star takes the spotlight this issue in a special chapter in which Shiina and Akira confront a Shadow Dragon master for the first time! The girls treat their alien starfish companions as friends -- but the creature they now face is controlled by a dark and twisted mind. Will they be able to defend themselves against such an experienced foe? In Oh My Goddess!, Keiichi and Belldandy get roped into helping Sayoko's art class -- but what they don't know is they're supposed to be nude models! Can Keiichi resist a classroom of women demanding he take his clothes off -- or does he even want to resist?! Plus, in Seraphic Feather,Japanese fan-favorite Hiroyuki Utatane draws another luscious chapter of interstellar romance and adventure; 3x3 Eyes features a special epilogue to the "Flight of the Demon" arc, in which our heroes make an important decision that takes the story to a new level. And two What's Michael? stories find our favorite feline frolicking with a stereo system and trying his hand at poker! Every issue, Super Manga Blast! brings you five full-length features for one low price, only from Dark Horse!

Round out your year with a giant serving of Super Manga Blast! This issues starts off with another Oh My Goddess! "lost" episode, as Keiichi plans for some romantic time alone with the goddess, Belldandy. Will his seaside excursion lead to their first kiss...or to disaster? In 3x3 Eyes, Pai is now a student and Yakumo is a homeless wanderer, frantically searching for his lost friend. Is this a different reality...or has something very strange happened to Pai and Yakumo? For hilarious comic relief -- not one, but four What's Michael? pieces grace this issue's pages! Plus, in Shadow Star, a murderous, maniacal teen has cornered Akira, while Shiina battles his deadly dragon! And in the science-fiction serial Seraphic Feather, Sunao gives the mysterious Attim M-Zak and Kei a lunar tour, winding up at a Chinese restaurant...and maybe winding up dead! Every issue of Super Manga Blast! brings you five full-length features for one low price, only from Dark Horse!

The latest episode of 3x3 Eyes finds a terrified Pai trapped in a dance hall filled with demon marionettes! Will this weirdness jolt her out of her amnesia? The fun in What's Michael? continues, as Michael again faces the horror of "The Guests Who Wouldn't Leave" and shows us his dancing skills in "The Ribbon." Enjoy a pulse-pounding segment of Shadow Star, with Shiina risking her life by confronting the murderer who's been terrorizing her friend Akira but with his flying dragon's help, he has his own deadly plan for her! Plus, mysteries abound in Seraphic Feather, over the powerful Emblem Seeds and the awesome abilities of the beautiful M-Zak, the Scarlet Angel, armed U.N. investigator! And in another "lost" episode of fan-favorite Oh My Goddess!, a rival motorcycle club has challenged the Nekomi Tech Motorcycle Club to a race?but the prize is the goddess Belldandy! Will the Nekomi Tech boys score enough wins to keep Belldandy as their mascot, or will the overconfident "Snapping Turtle" Etsushi get to take her away to his club?

America's favorite massive manga series continues! In the Oh My Goddess! cover story, Sayoko is still seething over losing her mantle as "campus queen" to the innocent Belldandy. Sayoko is desperate enough for attention that she'll even enter the Auto Club beauty contest! The mystical action in 3x3 Eyes continues, as Yakumo struggles to jog Pai's lost memory...and keep both of them alive as they try to escape from the deadly Marionettes of the Puppeteer's mansion! Feline hijinks abound in What's Michael? as Mari gets an adorable, attention-grabbing kitten, and her jealous boyfriend will try anything to scare it off! And in Shadow Star, a group of Dragon Child owners meet to discuss how to reshape the world...in their ownimages, while in Seraphic Feather, Attim M-Zak must fight for her life against Rix and his army of anti-personnel warfare robots, using her speed and sword-fighting skills to ward off a legion of machines! It's five stories for under five bucks!

In the final "lost" Oh My Goddess! story, Keiichi wants to give Belldandy a token of love for their first anniversary, but leave it to Urd to lead Keiichi down the wrong path! What do you buy the goddess who has everything? In 3x3 Eyes, Pai has finally opened her third eye, but she still can't remember her past, and the Sanjiyan is causing trouble when she's not "looking"! In our latest Shadow Star episode, Japan's military leaders gather in their base to discuss the mysterious and dangerous alien "shadow dragons." Assisting them is a strikingly beautiful and intelligent physicist who's also...Shiina's mom?! Seraphic Feather continues to mystify, as a corporate spy who knows the power of the Emblem Seed will stop at absolutely nothing to get to it, and in What's Michael?, those darn cats are nothing but trouble for an unfortunate bug and a pair of worrisome travelers.

BLACKEST NIGHT spreads with an oversized anniversary issue! Surrounded by friends and enemies, Hal Jordan goes into battle with a being he will never defeat - the Black Lantern Spectre! Can Saint Walker, Sinestro, and the others put a stop to this bizarre Spectre rebirth? 
 
Plus, Atrocitus reveals a tie to a power that may make him the most unbeatable of all the Lanterns!

description: A REALM OF KINGS ISSUE! Holy Octo-mom! What’s growing in Moondragon’s belly, why is the Universal Church of Truth obsessed with keeping her, and can the Guardians rescue her before the planet they’re on goes supernova? Find out in the series that IGN calls “Impressive…Brad Walker’s pages are a dazzling sight…Guardians of the Galaxy is still standing tall and strong.”
name: Happy Birthday

description: Since the shocking finale of SECRET INVASION vaulted him to national prominence and a newfound respect, Norman Osborn has been slowly organizing his power base, promoting his minions, eliminating his enemies - and losing his sanity. Now, as he meets with the uber-powerful elite of the Cabal - Doctor Doom, Loki and the Hood - the final stages of his Dark Reign are about to be put into fruition: the taking of Asgard. Some might say such a plan is insane. And when you're dealing with the former and possibly future Green Goblin, we're not going to disagree with you! SIEGE: STORMING OF ASGARD - HEROES & VILLIANS takes inside the careful planning behind Osborn's crusade to take the kingdom of Thor off the board. Who are the featured players in the saga, how did we get here, and what are the many contingencies in this operation? With insider character bios and commentary from the creators behind the Dark Siege, this will make essential reading for knocking off the events in style!

description: With Worf captured and under threat of execution, Geordi, Troi, and Dr. Crusher race to get information that will exonerate him. Picard and Riker negotiate with Worf's captors, but the paranoid warlords continue to regard all outsiders as a threat, and launch a military attack on the ship under the Enterprise's protection.

description:
Back Blurb

What more could anyone ask for than a Martian colony bursting its bustier with hundreds of super-stacked, dominating lesbian bitches descended from a repressed horde of super-models? Sounds like heaven, no? But there's trouble in paradise, as a gang of sexual rebels lusts for the touch of men -- and makes do with cucumbers and anything else they can find! Wonder how the cruel and powerful Queen Bitch will react to that? Just wait and see!

Meanwhile, back on Earth, rednecks led by the grungy gangster known as the "Couch Potato" deal dope, party, and screw mindlessly when not hounding a group of Yuppie scientists. The scientists are holding out as best they can while attempting to construct a spaceship out of used BMW parts so they can get to Mars -- where they know all the fun is!

With a wickedly funny, B-movie camp sensibility and non-stop sex action, Yuppies, Rednecks and Lesbian Bitches From Mars delivers the goods like few other series can. And with a title like that, how can you go wrong?
name: Yuppies, Rednecks, and Lesbian Bitches from Mars

description: “FRANKEN-CASTLE,” PART 3 Trapped in the dank tunnels under New York, surrounded by a savage team of Japanese monster hunters, filthy in the blood of his friends, Frank Castle turns, lifts a giant rifle and smiles. They aren’t prepared for this, you aren’t prepared for this, an entire issue loaded full, completely dedicated to bleeding, sweet, revenge-splattered murder in traditional hardcore Punisher style. Frank’s been through hell -- time to give a little back.

If you've never heard of Penny Arcade, it's possible you were killed tragically in a snowplow accident and your ghost is haunting the place where you once lived, convinced that you are still alive! Or you may have just missed out on this new invention called "the Internet." But don't fear, because Penny Arcade, the most popular web comic ever, is coming to comics shops and bookstores everywhere! The comic for gamers, by gamers is now available to everyone! In celebration of Dark Horse's January release of Attack of the Bacon Robots, the first Penny Arcade collection, we're offering readers a twenty-five-cent preview of the book in a twenty-four-page comic!

Give the gift of gold this season with the Gold Digger Christmas Special! Make your days merry and bright with a selection of heart-warming, high-powered holiday tales fromFred Perry and your other favorite A.P. artists. Be someone's special Santa this year (even your own) and get them a copy!

Make the holiday season happier with another Gold Digger Xmas Special for you and yours! Be good and give (or get) a gift of Gold Digger this Christmas!

description:
In the marketplace of Salaam Centaur, a city out of medieval fantasy, Kurt, a mercenary, strides toward a pre-arranged meeting. On the way, his coin purse is lifted by Sarah, a beggar. She repairs to her quarters, but soon finds the purse is missing, quietly retrieved by its owner.

Elsewhere in the city, Kit, an ambassador of the 'Phaerie' enters the domicile of Ororo, 'Goddess-of-the-Winds', pledging her services.

In a tavern, Kurt finds and meets Logan, a fellow mercenary. In synchronicity, Logan and Ororo each descibe to Kurt and Kit, respectively, the mission ahead of them: to eliminate a dark wizard who has been gathering and enslaving townsfolk, creating an army for himself.

As Logan and Kurt make their way out of the city, Sarah follows in the shadows, hoping to once again snatch the purse. Likewise, Ororo and Kit are trailed by a steel-skinned warrior. Outside the wizard's castle, the six come across each other, soon establishing they all share the same goal.

They enter the castle and face the wizard who invites them to join him. When they refuse, he orders his forces to attack. The battle is joined, but during the fray, Kurt catches a brief glimpse of the interior of a modern shopping mall. He tells the others what they are experiencing is an illusion. They quickly form a plan to take out the wizard.

Kurt approaches first, and becomes enthralled, but that allows Sarah to strike from behind, revealing the wizard is actually the X-Men's enemy, Mesmero. He quickly takes control of Sarah, and then the warrior, but Kit breaks though and knocks the villain unconscious.

The illusion fades, the mall reappears, and the customers come out of their hypnoses. Knowing they are likely to be blamed for what happened, Colossus scoops up Mesmero, and he, Marrow, Storm, Nightcrawler, Shadowcat and Wolverine make a hasty exit.
name: Thrall

description:
For over fifteen years, Gina Diggers has faced some of the strangest and deadliest forces and beings the universe can offer. Yet none have been so dangerous and implacable as her earliest foe, the dragon known as Dreadwing, First of Iron. Having suffered excruciating, humiliating defeat to his time-spanning ambitions from this mere human, Dreadwing has vowed to make Gina suffer like no other before he destroys her, but since an ancient, vastly powerful version of her emerged, it has made things...complicated.

To keep track of the delicious intricacy, subtlety and cleverness of his plans, Dreadwing has been logging them in his mymior, a draconic diary/computer/storehouse. In this full-color special, he reviews where he has been, what he has done, and what he must do next to ensure his greatest opponent loses, even if it means the end of the universe itself!
